# create Vagrant box
Im using Centos7 minimal

1. Install vagrant, virtual bix if not yet
vagrant version 1.9.0

2. Install Centos via virtual bix, as usually
	set root pass to vagrant
3. prepare centos
	set selinux to permissive
	add vagrant user
	create ~vagrant/.ssh/authorized_keys containing vagrant ssh pub key
	disable requiretty in sudoers
	grant sudo to root for vagrant user without password
	clean stuff: rm -f /var/log/wtmp /var/log/btmp and history -c
	poweroff
4. create vagrant box
	vagrant package --output centos7.box --base centos7
5. add vagrant box (not really clear for me yet why so)
	vagrant box add centos7 centos7.box

5a. Virtual machine in VirtualBox can be removed now

6. create vagrant project and configure vagrant file

vagrant init centos7
#will create Vagrantfile
add to Vagrantfile(will disable shared folders between machine and host):
config.vm.synced_folder ".", "/vagrant", id: "vagrant-root", disabled: true 

7. start vagrant
vagrant up

now can connect to vagrant box

vagrant ssh

other commands:
vagrant status
vagrant halt
vagrant destroy
